Durban - A 33-year-old man was killed when a tree fell onto him on an estate in Baynesfield, outside Pietermaritzburg on Monday. 
According to ER24, when they arrived at the scene, they found that the man had sustained a serious head injury and nothing more could be done for him. 

He was declared deceased at the scene. 
It is alleged that the man had been cutting a tree when he was struck by a falling branch. 
Provincial police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala, said Thornville police had opened an inquest docket.

She said the circumstances surrounding the incident are being investigated.
In a separate incident, six people were injured when their car rear-ended a bakkie on Sanctuary Road in Pietermaritzburg.
ER24 said the passengers that had been in the back of the vehicle were now found seated on the side of the road.

Medics assessed the patients and found that four people had sustained moderate while two others had sustained more serious injuries. Medics treated the patients and provided the two seriously injured with pain-relief medication before they were transported to Mediclinic Pietermaritzburg for further care.
The Mercury